{{{body}}}
    {{{h2}}}This is a sorting activity about your views on the factors that affected your responsiveness to university-based supervision provided by a doctoral supervisor.{{{/h2}}}
    {{{div class="instructions"}}}
        {{{div class="section"}}}
            {{{p}}}Supervisee responsiveness is defined as how supervisees engage with and react to feedback and guidance during supervision.{{{/p}}}
        {{{/div}}}
        {{{div class="section"}}}
            {{{p}}}Please see a list of statements that were created during the first step of the study. I request you to sort (i.e., drag and drop) each statement into the grid according to how significant you believe each statement is in defining the factors that impacted your responsiveness toward {{{span class="highlight"}}}UNIVERSITY-BASED INDIVIDUAL SUPERVISION EXPERIENCE{{{/span}}} with your {{{span class="highlight"}}}DOCTORAL SUPERVISOR{{{/span}}}.{{{/p}}}
        {{{/div}}}
        {{{div class="section"}}}
            {{{p}}}Please consider the supervisory process and the supervisor you took into account in the first step of the study, or (if new to the study) the supervisory process with a particular doctoral supervisor that has completed.{{{/p}}}
        {{{/div}}}
        {{{div class="section"}}}
            {{{p}}}There are two parts in this sorting activity:{{{/p}}}
            {{{ul}}}
                {{{li}}}On the next screen, you will be asked to pre-sort the statements into three piles:
                    {{{ul}}}
                        {{{li}}}A pile of statements you generally agree with,{{{/li}}}
                        {{{li}}}A pile of statements you generally disagree with,{{{/li}}}
                        {{{li}}}A pile for the rest.{{{/li}}}
                    {{{/ul}}}
                {{{/li}}}
                {{{li}}}Then, you will be asked to sort each of your three piles into a sorting grid. From left to right, the grid ranges from {{{span class="highlight"}}}least significant{{{/span}}} to {{{span class="highlight"}}}most significant{{{/span}}}.{{{/li}}}
            {{{/ul}}}
        {{{/div}}}
        {{{div class="section"}}}
            {{{p}}}You can make changes as often as you wish. Thank you for participating in this study.{{{/p}}}
        {{{/div}}}
    {{{/div}}}
{{{/body}}}
