Research Consent

Dear participant, thank you for participating the first round of research on "Supervisee Responsiveness". You are invited to participate in the second round of the research study conducted by Zubeyde Akpakir at Old Dominion University. Before you decide to participate, it is important that you understand why the research is being conducted and what it will involve. Please take the time to read the following information carefully. Feel free to contact the research team with any questions you may have. The purpose of this study is to understand the factors that affect supervisee responsiveness when supervision is provided by doctoral supervisors. If you agree to participate this round of the study, you will be asked to sort the statements regarding the factor affect supervisee responsiveness and then reflect on the sorting.  The study will take approximately 30 minutes. While there may not be direct benefits to you for participating, the information gathered from this study may help improve educational methods. All information collected in this study will be kept strictly confidential. Data will be stored securely and only the research team will have access to it. Your identity will not be disclosed in any reports or publications resulting from this study. Your participation in this study is entirely voluntary. You are free to decline to participate, or to withdraw at any time, without penalty or loss of benefits to which you are otherwise entitled. If you decide to withdraw, close the webpage and any data collected up to that point will be deleted.By clicking on the "Agree" button on the bottom of this page, you are indicating that you have read and understood the information provided, and that you agree to participate in this study. If you have any questions about this study, please contact Zubeyde Akpakir at zakpa001@odu.edu

Contact Information

Thank you for participating in this dissertation research project. You can contact Zubeyde Akpakir  at zakpa001@odu.edu or the dissertation chair of this study Dr. Gulsah Kemer at gkemer@odu.edu . 
































